       width = 31;
     }
     return (1ULL << width) & 0xFFFFFFFF;
   }
   ```
   
   GLOBAL FIX:
   
   A more thorough root-cause fix is to ensure that the shift count is always
   within the bounds of the int operand. This can be achieved by using a type
   that is large enough to hold the shift count, such as an unsigned long long.
   
   ```diff
   uint32_t high_bit_mask(uint64_t width) {
     return (1ULL << width) & 0xFFFFFFFF;
   }
   ```
   
   However, if we need to keep the width as an int, we can still fix this by
   ensuring that the shift count does not exceed the width of the int operand.
   We can do this by using the maximum value of the int type (INT_MAX) as the
   maximum shift count.
   
   ```diff
   uint32_t high_bit_mask(int width) {
     return (1ULL << (width > INT_MAX? INT_MAX : width)) & 0xFFFFFFFF;
   }
   ```
